Cape Town trains are reportedly in disarray. eNCA's Nobesuthu Hejana reports. Courtesy of #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - Around 80 percent of train stations in Gauteng lie in ruins and it is a similar case in the Western Cape. Train stations across the country were stripped of anything of value after the country was placed on lockdown last year. READ: Prasa heads to court over homes on Cape Town train tracks In Cape Town, there are calls for urgent intervention to address the dilapidated Netreg train station. It’s part of Cape Town's busy Central Line, which hasn’t been operational since 2019, due to constant vandalism. Meanwhile, Prasa’s been on a drive in various parts of the country to assess infrastructure.